Sec. 165.041. GENERAL PENALTY. (a) A person commits an
offense if the person violates a provision of Subchapter B of this
chapter or a rule adopted under that subchapter.
(b) An offense under this section is a Class C misdemeanor
unless it is shown on the trial of the offense that the defendant has
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 951 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

been previously convicted under this section, in which event the
offense is a Class B misdemeanor.
(c) A person commits a separate offense for each day of
violation.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1430, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 836, Sec. 51, eff. Sept. 1,
1989; Acts 1993, 73rd Leg., ch. 548, Sec. 20, eff. Sept. 1, 1993.

